        <td bgcolor="black" colspan="2"  valign="top">
		<img src="icon_posticon.gif" border="0" hspace="3"><font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2">Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;07/18/2002&nbsp;:&nbsp; 03:53:03</font>

		&nbsp;<a href="pop_profile.asp?mode=display&amp;id=4267"><img src="icon_profile.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Show Profile" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>
 
			&nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_mail.asp?id=4267')"><img src="icon_email.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Email Poster" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=TopicQuote&amp;TOPIC_ID=6152&amp;FORUM_ID=2&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=General+Discussions&amp;Topic_Title=Pets+and+Resists"><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2"> Hi,</P><P>  We've had a change up on Test for about a week, and I wanted to share it with you guys and see what you think.  Here's the basis of the change -</P><P><b>When a pet is hit with a spell, it uses the resistances and level of it's owner to see if it resists the spell.</b></P><P>  This means that if you're a level 60 magician for instance and you've got on various buffs and gear that raise your resistances, your pet will save vs. spells as if it was also level 60 with your exact resistance scores.</P><P>  Using the owner's level is going to make a huge difference in how well the pet resists harmful spells, and should make a noticeable difference in how well the pets can survive AEs for instance.  Allowing the pet to also benefit from your items and buffs means that it will be living a lot longer when fighting casters.</P><P>  There is a drawback to this, although I think the good outweighs the bad.  If we go with this new scheme, it will mean that the pet always uses the owner's saves.  Some types of pets currently are highly resistant to poison or disease for instance.  Going with the new scheme would mean they will potentially not resist those types of spells as well, depending on the owner's resistances.</P><P>  Overall, this change would mean that pets are much more resistant the vast majority of the time.  I think this would be a very positive change for pet classes, but I'd like to see what people think before we go ahead with it.</P><P>  Thanks for your time,</P><P>- Rich</P><P> </font></td>

      </tr>

