        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         I'm glad to see you're asking for comments before this change is made.</P><P>First, before you do this, you need to look at how this will affect certain encounters which currently depend on mage pet resistances. The shaman epic mob in CoM for example, has a 1100dd fire AoE, and the common tactic is to have two mage fire pets tank him, as they are immune to fire. This change would make that mob very, very hard for its level, and affect the entire shaman epic quest as a result.</P><P>If there was a way to code pets into keeping their innate resistances (by the way... I have not noticed necromancer pets to have ANY innate resistances worth speaking of, whereas mage pets have all sorts), it would be a much better situation all around.</P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=81496">Dolalin</a> Bonewielder<BR>Warlock of <a href="http://www.theshadoworder.com">The Shadow Order</a><BR><a href="http://pub4.ezboard.com/beqasylum">Lanys T`Vyl</a><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
